{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/recipes/3-2-1-pie-crust","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>This is the easy and famous '3, 2, 1' pie crust.  It's 3 parts flour, 2 parts fat, and 1 part liquid - along with some salt and/or sugar for flavor.  Those who have read my post on <a href=\"http://www.eastmeetskitchen.com/blog/ratio-a-book-review.html\">ratios</a> know that these \"parts\" are by weight and not volume, so this is when owning a <a href=\"http://www.eastmeetskitchen.com/tips/scale-a-must-have.html\">scale</a> becomes useful.  </p>\n<p>The recipe comes out flakey and delicious every time.  I <a href=\"http://www.eastmeetskitchen.com/tips/grating-your-butter.html\">grate the butter</a> instead of using my fingers, which is less messy.  The dough is also freezable, so if you buy a couple disposable pie tins and press the dough in, you have pie crusts ready to go!</p>\n<p>So this year, instead of buying pies from the store for Thanksgiving or Christmas, make it from scratch.  It's nicer, homier, and much more impressive.</p>\n<p><strong>Directions</strong></p>\n<p><strong>1. Combine flour, salt, and sugar in a bowl.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/7ee88bc7bc634bf3e15d0b2f998de7a9/f9294/113-2.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"113 2\" title=\"113 2\" src=\"/static/7ee88bc7bc634bf3e15d0b2f998de7a9/f9294/113-2.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/7ee88bc7bc634bf3e15d0b2f998de7a9/90185/113-2.jpg 450w,\n/static/7ee88bc7bc634bf3e15d0b2f998de7a9/f9294/113-2.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p><strong>2. Grate butter into dry ingredients.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 726px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/8b60e39d6d64203914e166555e2b2073/4e1b0/113-3.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"113 3\" title=\"113 3\" src=\"/static/8b60e39d6d64203914e166555e2b2073/4e1b0/113-3.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/8b60e39d6d64203914e166555e2b2073/90185/113-3.jpg 450w,\n/static/8b60e39d6d64203914e166555e2b2073/4e1b0/113-3.jpg 726w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p><strong>3. Put dry ingredients and butter into the freezer for 5 minutes.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 726px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/efd82ccbd18db95c771d8f0d726880d7/4e1b0/113-5.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"113 5\" title=\"113 5\" src=\"/static/efd82ccbd18db95c771d8f0d726880d7/4e1b0/113-5.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/efd82ccbd18db95c771d8f0d726880d7/90185/113-5.jpg 450w,\n/static/efd82ccbd18db95c771d8f0d726880d7/4e1b0/113-5.jpg 726w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p><strong>4. Take out dry ingredients and pour in water.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/c8c6aae1fbf35a72541cf438ccdde969/f9294/113-4.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"113 4\" title=\"113 4\" src=\"/static/c8c6aae1fbf35a72541cf438ccdde969/f9294/113-4.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/c8c6aae1fbf35a72541cf438ccdde969/90185/113-4.jpg 450w,\n/static/c8c6aae1fbf35a72541cf438ccdde969/f9294/113-4.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p><strong>5. Using a fork, mix until dough comes together.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/dd4b7c3c140e96fbe8b5bc308823d532/f9294/113-6.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"113 6\" title=\"113 6\" src=\"/static/dd4b7c3c140e96fbe8b5bc308823d532/f9294/113-6.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/dd4b7c3c140e96fbe8b5bc308823d532/90185/113-6.jpg 450w,\n/static/dd4b7c3c140e96fbe8b5bc308823d532/f9294/113-6.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p><strong>6. Dough can be frozen for several weeks.  If choosing to par bake, bake for 20 minutes at 375 degrees Fahrenheit.</strong></p>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 726px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/a8b44320e03e2f0b6ec27749d7eb7f52/4e1b0/113-7.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"113 7\" title=\"113 7\" src=\"/static/a8b44320e03e2f0b6ec27749d7eb7f52/4e1b0/113-7.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/a8b44320e03e2f0b6ec27749d7eb7f52/90185/113-7.jpg 450w,\n/static/a8b44320e03e2f0b6ec27749d7eb7f52/4e1b0/113-7.jpg 726w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<section class=\"recipe\">\n<p><strong>Ingredients</strong></p></section>\n<p>(Makes 1 9-inch pie shell)</p>\n<ul><li>1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li><li>1/4 teaspoon fine salt</li><li>1 teaspoon granulated sugar</li><li>1 stick unsalted butter, frozen</li><li>5 tablespoons ice water</li></ul></section>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"This is the easy and famous '3, 2, 1' pie crust.  It's 3 parts flour, 2 parts fat, and 1 part liquid - along with some salt and/or sugar forâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"'3 2 1' Pie Crust","image":{"feature":{"publicURL":"/static/113-1-4f95f9ed5204d54a75763468a70381fd.jpg","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5008517887563884,"src":"/static/4f95f9ed5204d54a75763468a70381fd/b17c1/113-1.jpg","srcSet":"/static/4f95f9ed5204d54a75763468a70381fd/00e5e/113-1.jpg 200w,\n/static/4f95f9ed5204d54a75763468a70381fd/1a903/113-1.jpg 400w,\n/static/4f95f9ed5204d54a75763468a70381fd/b17c1/113-1.jpg 800w,\n/static/4f95f9ed5204d54a75763468a70381fd/33881/113-1.jpg 881w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"feature_video":null,"date":"2014-11-19","categories":["recipes"],"tags":["recipes","sweets","pie crust"]},"fields":{"slug":"/recipes/3-2-1-pie-crust","date":"2014-11-19T00:00:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/recipes/3-2-1-pie-crust","nextslug":"/blog/the-new-union-square-donuts-opens","prevslug":"/tips/grating-your-butter"}}}